Subject: Re: [T2] Studs vs bolts

It's also a lot easier to crack the frozen nut off a stud than it is to
remove a frozen stud from an aluminum case. Much easier to dress stud
threads than install an insert.
Heat and paraffin (the USA kind, not UK) are your friends for stuck stuff,
especially steel into aluminum.

